node.title: Watch: PM speaks in Auckland during first visit since Delta lockdown
node.description: The Prime Minister speaks in Auckland.
node.content: ["This livestream has finished.\u00a0", "Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern is speaking to reporters in Auckland during her first visit to the city since it was locked down almost three months ago.\u00a0", "It also comes after a large march at Parliament on Tuesday, with protesters expressing anger about lockdown restrictions and vaccine mandates.\u00a0", "Auckland is still at alert level 3, but step 2 rules came into force on Wednesday, meaning retail stores and public venues can open, and outdoor gatherings of up to 25 people are allowed.\u00a0", "Watch the video.\u00a0"]
